cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.HC

This paper focuses on analyzing user behavior and motivations across different language editions of Wikipedia, which involves aspects of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) to match survey responses with server logs. The study also examines the socio-economic characteristics of countries where certain Wikipedia use cases are more prevalent, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
